-- Airbus wins $1.6 bln Saudi Arabian plane order
-- 
-- Mon Jul 14, 2008 7:36am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/14/us-airshow-airbus-saudiarabia-idUSL1462645520080714

 

 FARNBOROUGH  (Reuters) - European planemaker Airbus ( EAD.PA ) won a firm order for eight A330-300 widebody aircraft from State-owned Saudi Arabian Airlines SAUD.UL, Airbus said at the Farnborough Airshow on Monday. 

 The deal is worth about $1.6 billion at list prices. (Reporting by  James Regan )